---

### Summary

Issue #280 was mostly implemented in PR #664 (merged). All 4 acceptance criteria are met. However, the UX design spec (Section 7) explicitly shows an **"Add" submit button** in the form — this was never added. Without it, users must press Enter to submit, which silently fails when focus is on the `<select>` element in some browsers.

### Metadata

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Complexity | LOW |
| Files to UPDATE | 2 |
| Total Tasks | 2 |

### Key Patterns Discovered

- Submit button pattern: `MobileFAB.tsx:74-80` — `type="submit"`, `bg-primary text-on-primary disabled:opacity-50`
- Button click test pattern: `Sidebar.test.tsx:356` — `fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: 'Add' }))`
- UX spec: `docs/ux-design-spec.html:2058` — confirms "Add" button right-aligned in second form row

### UX Transformation

- **BEFORE**: Form submits only via Enter key; fails silently when `<select>` has focus
- **AFTER**: Explicit "Add" button provides discoverable save affordance; works from any focused field

### Risks

- **Button text ambiguity in tests**: Low — use `getByRole('button', { name: 'Add' })` to scope correctly

### Confidence Score

**9/10** for one-pass implementation success — the change is 5 lines of JSX + 1 new test; exact insertion point and button code are specified with direct source references.
